27/01/2010
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- Serbia's Deputy Minister for Kosovo Branislav Ristic on Tuesday (January 26th) was expelled to Serbia after being arrested by police Special Forces. Ristic was detained while holding an unannounced political meeting on Kosovo territory. He, along with two other Serb citizens and three Kosovo Serbs, were questioned by police in the village of Dreshnike/Drsnik in Klina, central Kosovo. Charges will be pressed against the Serb citizens for illegal border crossing. The police action faced resistance by local Serbs, media reported. (Zeri, Koha Ditore, Kosova Sot - 27/01/10; Kohavision, RTK, Klan Kosova - 26/01/10)
